这让我成了这个年龄段最难让人接受的女人
Which makes me the most irresponsible
woman of my age that I know.

524
00:55:47,151 --> 00:55:49,861
你不用拿个杯子吗?
Would you like a glass for that?

525
00:55:49,903 --> 00:55:51,445
不,谢谢
No, thank you.

526
00:55:55,992 --> 00:55:58,410
你知道,你很搞笑
You know, you were very funny.

527
00:55:58,452 --> 00:56:00,995
你的手抖的很厉害
Your hands were shaking
about a mile a minute.

528
00:56:04,457 --> 00:56:06,458
还没结束
This isn't over.

529
00:56:06,584 --> 00:56:08,919
我十分的恐惧
I'm absolutely terrified.

530
00:56:13,923 --> 00:56:17,050
尽是些我们无法理解的事情
It's all the things
that we don't understand.

531
00:56:19,762 --> 00:56:22,931
我感觉,那些猿人从原始森林走出来...
I feel like the protohuman,
coming out of the forest primeval...

532
00:56:23,056 --> 00:56:26,350
第一会看见了月亮,向它仍石子
and seeing the moon for the first time
and throwing rocks at it.

533
00:56:26,476 --> 00:56:29,853
如果我被杀了,我能回来...
If I got killed,
would I come back...

534
00:56:29,895 --> 00:56:32,855
像我的女儿一样被陷在房子里吗?
and get stuck in the house
like my sister?

535
00:56:32,898 --> 00:56:34,649
你妹妹没死
Your sister isn't dead, Robbie.

536
00:56:34,774 --> 00:56:36,650
如果我被杀了...
If I got killed...

537
00:56:36,776 --> 00:56:39,861
我能去看望她,告诉如何出来吗?
could I visit her
and show her how to get back here?

538
00:56:39,904 --> 00:56:42,781
你可以系跟绳子在我身上,紧紧的拉住...
You could tie a rope around me
and hold it tight...

539
00:56:42,781 --> 00:56:47,326
那么人们就可以拉住我们不让我们陷进去
then somebody could come and get us,
and we could live somewhere else.

540
00:56:49,745 --> 00:56:51,871
有人相信...
Some people believe...

541
00:56:51,914 --> 00:56:54,791
人死后灵魂会升入天堂
that when you die,
your soul goes to heaven.

542
00:56:54,916 --> 00:56:56,917
外公死时...
When Grandpa was dead...

543
00:56:56,918 --> 00:57:00,629
我在医院的病床上看着他...
I looked at him in the hospital bed
and I was watching...

544
00:57:00,629 --> 00:57:03,214
但是我没有见到有东西从他身上升起来
but I didn't see anything
go up out of him.

545
00:57:03,340 --> 00:57:06,467
罗比,他的灵魂是看不见的
His soul is invisible, Robbie.
You couldn't see it.

546
00:57:06,509 --> 00:57:09,469
但是外公为什么不和卡罗尔一起出现在电视上呢?
But how come Grandpa isn't
on television with Carol Anne?

547
00:57:10,680 --> 00:57:13,557
有人相信人死后...
Some people believe
that when people die...

548
00:57:15,084 --> 00:57:17,545
有个非常棒的灯...
there's a wonderful light...

549
00:57:17,629 --> 00:57:19,672
和太阳一样明亮...
as bright as the sun...

550
00:57:19,797 --> 00:57:22,842
并且并不刺眼
but it doesn't hurt
to look into it.

551
00:57:22,926 --> 00:57:26,513
你所想知道所有问题的所有答案...
All the answers to all the questions
that you ever want to know...

552
00:57:26,554 --> 00:57:29,098
都在这灯里面
are inside that light.

553
00:57:29,140 --> 00:57:33,269
而当你走向它，你就永远成了它的一部分
And when you walk to it,
you become a part of it forever.

554
00:57:34,646 --> 00:57:37,106
然后，一些人死了...
And then, some people die...

555
00:57:37,232 --> 00:57:39,692
但是他们自己并不知道
but they don't know
that they've gone.

556
00:57:41,694 --> 00:57:43,446
他们以为他们自己还活着?
They think they're still alive?

557
00:57:46,324 --> 00:57:49,118
是的，可能他们并不想死
Maybe they didn't want to die.

558
00:57:49,160 --> 00:57:51,412
可能他们还没有准备好
Maybe they weren't ready.

559
00:57:51,538 --> 00:57:53,414
可能他们还没活够...
Maybe they hadn't
lived fully yet...

560
00:57:53,540 --> 00:57:57,585
或者他们已经活了很长时间，
但是他们还想继续活下去
or they'd lived a long time,
but they still wanted more life.

561
00:57:57,585 --> 00:58:00,964
他们拒绝走向那个灯光...
They resist going into that light...

562
00:58:01,005 --> 00:58:04,342
无论那个灯多需要他们
however hard the light wants them.

563
00:58:04,425 --> 00:58:07,428
他们留在了附近...
They just hang around...

564
00:58:07,428 --> 00:58:11,724
看电视，看着他们的朋友长大...
watch TV,
watch their friends grow up...

565
00:58:11,766 --> 00:58:15,270
感到不开心和嫉妒
feeling unhappy and jealous.

566
00:58:15,311 --> 00:58:18,189
那些感情很不好
Those feelings are bad.

567
00:58:18,273 --> 00:58:19,983
他们感到受伤害了
They hurt.

568
00:58:21,901 --> 00:58:24,153
然后...
And then...

569
00:58:24,195 --> 00:58:26,489
那些人...
some people...

570
00:58:26,614 --> 00:58:30,326
失去了前往灯光的道路...
just get lost
on the way to the light...

571
00:58:30,451 --> 00:58:34,163
他们需要有人来引导他们
and they need someone
to guide them to it.

572
00:58:34,205 --> 00:58:36,749
所以那些人生气了...
So some people get angry...

573
00:58:36,875 --> 00:58:39,502
并乱扔东西，像我的卧室一样?
and throw things around,
like in my bedroom?

574
00:58:42,088 --> 00:58:44,507
就像在学校
Just like in school.

575
00:58:44,632 --> 00:58:47,218
一些小朋友对你很好...
Like, some kids are nice to you...

576
00:58:47,302 --> 00:58:49,220
另一些对你刻薄
some kids are mean.

577
00:58:49,304 --> 00:58:51,973
我有一次被3个小孩打了
I got beat up once
by three kids.

578
00:58:52,056 --> 00:58:53,975
他们拿走了我的午饭钱
They took my lunch money.

579
00:58:54,058 --> 00:58:57,353
可能他们被卡车撞了，现在正在楼上呢
Maybe they got hit by a truck,
and they're upstairs right now.

580
00:58:57,478 --> 00:59:01,357
听着, 也许我们该睡觉了，好吗?
Listen, partner, maybe we oughta
get some shut-eye, okay?

581
00:59:02,525 --> 00:59:04,068
你知道吗?
You know what?

582
00:59:04,110 --> 00:59:06,237
当我们告诉奶奶今晚...
When we called Grandma tonight...

583
00:59:06,362 --> 00:59:09,240
她很兴奋你打算去陪她...
she got really excited that
you're comin' to stay with her...

584
00:59:09,282 --> 00:59:13,286
她打算好好接待你们
and she's plannin' all these
neat things for you guys to do.

585
00:59:13,369 --> 00:59:15,663
我可以带E. Buzz和我一起去吗?
Can I take E. Buzz with me
when we go?

586
00:59:15,663 --> 00:59:17,999
当然可以
Sure you can.

587
00:59:18,082 --> 00:59:20,502
- 晚安，妈妈
- 晚安，亲爱的
- Good night, Mom.
- Good night, sweetie.

588
00:59:20,543 --> 00:59:22,212
晚安，女士
Night, lady.

589
00:59:24,297 --> 00:59:25,715
晚安，爸爸
Night, Dad.

590
00:59:26,633 --> 00:59:28,218
晚安, 罗比.
Night, Rob.

591
00:59:29,385 --> 00:59:31,137
我爱你
I love you.

592
00:59:32,722 --> 00:59:34,849
晚安, 卡罗尔.
Good night, Carol Anne.

593
01:00:33,199 --> 01:00:35,743
我想去找点吃的
I'm gonna go
get something to eat.

594
01:06:01,986 --> 01:06:04,739
那是什么?
What is it?

595
01:06:21,756 --> 01:06:23,174
回放一下
Roll it back.

596
01:06:28,429 --> 01:06:30,723
我想我们应该已经录下来了
I think we got one.
I think it recorded.

597
01:06:37,146 --> 01:06:39,315
是的，录下来了
Yes. It recorded.

598
01:06:57,167 --> 01:06:59,502
看看他们所有人
Look at all of them.

599
01:06:59,586 --> 01:07:01,504
那是我们的房子吗?
Is that our house?

600
01:07:05,216 --> 01:07:07,177
那些人是谁?
Who are all those people?

601
01:07:08,178 --> 01:07:11,306
他们是这样孤独，这样孤独
They're so alone. So alone.

602
01:07:16,644 --> 01:07:18,646
他们从哪里来?
Where are they coming from?

603
01:07:20,356 --> 01:07:21,774
我不知道
I don't know.

604
01:07:55,099 --> 01:07:57,393
打电话给我，好吗?
Call me, okay?

605
01:08:03,650 --> 01:08:05,860
这块宝石已经有一百多年的历史了
This cameo is over
a hundred years old.

606
01:08:06,986 --> 01:08:08,446
是的，挺长时间了?
Yeah, some haul, huh?

607
01:08:08,571 --> 01:08:11,991
而这块表只有几年的历史，而它不是你们的
And this watch is only
a few years old, and it's not yours.

608
01:08:13,868 --> 01:08:15,537
嗯，我先走了
Well, I'm off.

609
01:08:15,578 --> 01:08:18,540
我要带着这些东西和录像带去实验室
I'm taking these back to the lab
along with the tapes.

610
01:08:19,958 --> 01:08:22,710
你知道，我不得不展示它们
I'm going to have to
display these, you know.

611
01:08:22,752 --> 01:08:25,755
- 请不要再“60分钟”上面
- 或是“难以置信”
- Please, not on "60 Minutes."
- Or "That's Incredible!"

612
01:08:25,880 --> 01:08:28,758
对不起
I'll get it. Excuse me.

613
01:08:48,027 --> 01:08:50,321
我会把赖安留在这里陪你
I'm leaving Ryan here with you.

614
01:08:51,447 --> 01:08:53,491
马蒂不会回来了
Marty won't be coming back.

615
01:08:58,788 --> 01:09:01,040
我会回来的
I am coming back.

616
01:09:06,087 --> 01:09:08,173
并且我会带回来一些有帮助的东西
And I'll bring some help.

617
01:09:08,214 --> 01:09:10,175
不要担心
Try not to worry.

618
01:09:14,179 --> 01:09:15,930
谢谢你
Thank you.

619
01:09:15,930 --> 01:09:17,932
我们在办公室很想你
We've missed you
down at the office.

620
01:09:18,057 --> 01:09:22,770
小伙子们很担心，所以我过来看看--
The boys have gotten worried,
so I took it upon myself to--

621
01:09:22,812 --> 01:09:26,065
天啊，史迪夫, 你看上去很糟糕
你现在感到好点了吗?
Jesus, Steve, you look like shit.
Aren't you feeling any better?

622
01:09:26,107 --> 01:09:29,652
我还是感到很虚弱，逖格先生
我感冒了，我起不来--
I'm still weak, Mr. Teague.
I've got the flu, I can't get up--

623
01:09:29,694 --> 01:09:32,238
你这里看上去好像有线电视坏了
Looks like you got
some cable problems here.

624
01:09:32,363 --> 01:09:35,408
是的，有线坏了几个星期了
Yeah. The cable's been off
for a couple of weeks.

625
01:09:35,533 --> 01:09:38,536
我们应该查一查。
这个街区的其他用户也坏了吗?
We'll have to look into that.
The rest of the block dark too?

626
01:09:38,620 --> 01:09:41,956
不，只是我们
No, just us.

627
01:09:42,081 --> 01:09:45,251
你这里电路好像也有点问题
You got some electrical problems
as well here.

628
01:09:45,293 --> 01:09:48,922
你把什么东西装这里了，300瓦的灯泡?
What have you got screwed in there,
a 300-watt bulb?

629
01:09:48,963 --> 01:09:50,965
你怕遭贼，或是打算吸引...
You afraid of burglars,
or are you trying to attract...

630
01:09:50,965 --> 01:09:52,967
在佛得角山脉的所有昆虫?
every insect in Cuesta Verde?

631
01:09:54,511 --> 01:09:57,514
- 史迪夫, 你在这里开心吗?
- 是的，先生
- Steve, are you happy here?
- Yes, I am, sir.

632
01:09:57,555 --> 01:09:59,682
恕我冒昧问这些问题...
Forgive me for asking
all these questions...

633
01:09:59,807 --> 01:10:02,644
但我们不想失去我们最好的职员...
but we don't want to lose
the best rep we've ever had...

634
01:10:02,685 --> 01:10:05,855
因为感冒或是其他问题
to the flu
or other opportunities.

635
01:10:05,980 --> 01:10:08,525
看了你起居室里的所有软件...
Seeing all that software
in your living room...

636
01:10:08,566 --> 01:10:12,153
使我怀疑，也许你已经
得出点什么东西了
makes me wonder, maybe you've
got something going on the side.

637
01:10:12,153 --> 01:10:14,697
不，我只是在看 “普通机械学”
我有这嗜好
No, I just read "Popular Mechanics."
I got hobbies.

638
01:10:14,822 --> 01:10:16,824
想兜兜风吗?
Feel like going
for a little ride?

639
01:10:16,866 --> 01:10:18,826
我有点东西想给你看
I'd like to show you something.

640
01:11:06,624 --> 01:11:11,045
哦，天啊! 对不起!
Oh, God! I'm sorry!

641
01:11:13,756 --> 01:11:16,759
你的一个孩子是在这屋子
里生下来的，对吗?
One of your children
was born in your house, huh?

642
01:11:20,346 --> 01:11:24,100
我理解她错过了很多学校
I understand that she's
missed a lot of school.

643
01:11:24,225 --> 01:11:27,937
崔斯克的一个女儿也是在同一个护士班
One of Trask's daughters
is in the same nursery class.

644
01:11:28,062 --> 01:11:30,231
她也感冒了，是吗?
She got the flu as well, huh?

645
01:11:30,231 --> 01:11:32,233
是的，我们都感冒了
Yeah, we've all got
the same thing.

646
01:11:32,317 --> 01:11:33,484
对不起
I'm sorry.

647
01:11:34,527 --> 01:11:37,947
- 我没看到她
- 她就在附近
- I didn't see her.
- She's around.

648
01:11:37,947 --> 01:11:41,784
我想，你不介意我问你个问题吧
I wonder if you'd mind
if I asked you a question.

649
01:11:41,826 --> 01:11:44,245
你是不是打算离开佛得角山脉?
Are you thinking about
leaving Cuesta Verde?

650
01:11:45,997 --> 01:11:49,209
为什么这世界上的所有人在这样
的一天都会有个问题？
How could anyone in the world
have a problem...

651
01:11:49,248 --> 01:11:51,208
on a day like this?

652
01:11:53,421 --> 01:11:56,090
这个位置放个落地窗不错吧?
How's that spot
for a bay window?

653
01:11:58,510 --> 01:12:01,095
你住在这里的话是不错，但是...
It's pretty nice if you're
living up here, but...

654
01:12:02,138 --> 01:12:04,098
对于山谷里来说...
not so great
down in the valley...

655
01:12:04,140 --> 01:12:06,267
看到山上有人家，就不怎么好看了
Looking at homes
cutting into the hillside.

656
01:12:06,392 --> 01:12:08,686
你不需要继续住在山谷里了
You don't have to live
in the valley anymore.

657
01:12:10,396 --> 01:12:11,981
你说什么?
What are you saying?

658
01:12:12,106 --> 01:12:14,692
我们将在我们现在站的地方开始5个阶段
We're starting phase five
right here where we're standing.

659
01:12:14,734 --> 01:12:17,695
这里可以成为你的主卧室套间
All of this can be
your master bedroom suite.

660
01:12:17,737 --> 01:12:20,406
那里可以成为你的观景台，
有兴趣吗?
That can be your view.
Interested?

661
01:12:23,159 --> 01:12:25,161
嗯，逖格先生，你真大方阿
Well, Mr. Teague,
that's a generous offer.

662
01:12:26,830 --> 01:12:30,041
- 我不是个开发商
- 你负责 42% 的销售
- I'm just not a developer.
- You're responsible for 42o/o of sales.

663
01:12:30,166 --> 01:12:32,460
那几乎是下面所有的一半了
That's almost half
of everything down there.

664
01:12:32,585 --> 01:12:36,005
几乎是价值7千万美元的房产
Almost $70 million worth
of dwelling and properties.

665
01:12:36,130 --> 01:12:38,550
那是一整套安全的发展计划...
That's a whole generation
of security...

666
01:12:38,591 --> 01:12:40,844
没人可以往上面贴价格标签
that nobody
can put a price tag on.

667
01:12:40,885 --> 01:12:45,306
我认为我们应该3年前就使你
成为我们的完全合伙人
I know we should have made you
a full partner three years ago.

668
01:12:45,348 --> 01:12:47,308
我现在不想失去你
I don't want to lose you now.

669
01:12:53,356 --> 01:12:56,901
这里没有空间造个游泳池吧?
Not much room
for a pool, is there?

670
01:12:56,985 --> 01:12:59,195
我们有整块土地
We own all the land.

671
01:12:59,279 --> 01:13:02,323
我们已经有了重新安排墓地的协议
We've already made arrangements
for relocating the cemetery.

672
01:13:04,200 --> 01:13:05,493
你在开玩笑吧
You're kidding me.

673
01:13:05,618 --> 01:13:09,330
- 这会遭天遣的，不是吗?
- 哦，不要担心
- That's sacrilegious, isn't it?
- Oh, don't worry about it.

674
01:13:09,372 --> 01:13:13,042
毕竟，这不是古代部落的墓场
After all, it's not ancient
tribal burial ground.

675
01:13:13,084 --> 01:13:15,378
这只是...人
It's just... people.

676
01:13:16,671 --> 01:13:18,673
另外，我们以前也做过
Besides, we've done it before.

677
01:13:20,091 --> 01:13:21,301
什么时候?
When?

678
01:13:21,342 --> 01:13:24,304
76年，就在山谷里
In '76. Right down there.

679
01:13:30,059 --> 01:13:31,519
佛得角山脉?
Cuesta Verde?

680
01:13:31,603 --> 01:13:34,480
总共300亩土地，挺大的生意
All 300 acres.
It was quite a deal.

681
01:13:34,522 --> 01:13:36,608
我从没听说过
But I never heard
anything about it.

682
01:13:36,649 --> 01:13:39,194
这又不值得在广告牌上登广告...
It's not something
one advertises on a billboard...

683
01:13:39,235 --> 01:13:41,237
或是登在汽车上
or on the side of a bus.

684
01:13:41,237 --> 01:13:46,496
不要担心，朋友和亲属可以
在布朗斯顿公墓看望故去的人
Don't worry. Friends and relatives
can visit their loved ones...
in Broxton Memorial Park.

685
01:13:46,534 --> 01:13:48,536
只有5分钟的路程
It's only five minutes further.

686
01:13:48,620 --> 01:13:51,372
哦，是的，5分钟路程，不太远
Oh, yeah. Five minutes.
That's no great hardship.

687
01:13:53,416 --> 01:13:55,376
我想应该没问题
I suppose that would be okay.

688
01:13:56,669 --> 01:13:57,962
谁没问题?
Okay with whom?

689
01:13:59,839 --> 01:14:01,382
可能会抱怨的人
Whomever might complain.

690
01:14:02,842 --> 01:14:04,844
现在为止都没人抱怨
Nobody's complained until now.

691
01:14:24,739 --> 01:14:28,827
我们在厨房有两种经历，这里是房间
We've had two experiences
in the kitchen. This is the den.

692
01:14:39,754 --> 01:14:41,714
你们不要跟过来好吗?
Y'all mind hangin' back?

693
01:14:41,756 --> 01:14:43,716
你们会干扰我的频率
You're jammin' my frequencies.

694
01:15:32,891 --> 01:15:36,936
那么... 我们今晚研究彩虹的
哪一边, 莱斯博士?
So... what side of the rainbow
are we working tonight, Dr. Lesh?

695
01:15:39,689 --> 01:15:43,067
- 这就是你的解决方案?
- 我知道你在想什么
- This your Knott's Berry Farm solution?
- I know what you're thinking.

696
01:15:43,109 --> 01:15:47,363
但是你要记住我的话，她已经
驱清了很多屋子的鬼
But you must take my word for it.
She's cleaned many houses.

697
01:15:47,405 --> 01:15:49,365
她的能力有所记载--
Her gifts have been documented--

698
01:15:49,407 --> 01:15:51,701
那晚以后，我们没再听见过卡罗尔
We haven't heard Carol Anne
since last night.

699
01:15:51,826 --> 01:15:53,953
这门为什么锁了，富勒里先生?
Why is this door locked,
Mr. Freeling?

700
01:15:58,541 --> 01:16:00,668
- 回答她, 史迪夫.
- 我会的
- Answer her, Steven.
- I am.

701
01:16:03,213 --> 01:16:05,673
我是说那个起居室
I am addressing the living.

702
01:16:06,382 --> 01:16:08,384
对不起
I'm sorry.

703
01:16:08,426 --> 01:16:10,845
那个房间是我的儿子和女儿住的
That's the room
my son and daughter used to occupy.

704
01:16:10,970 --> 01:16:12,931
我们相信那是这个屋子的心脏
We believe it's the heart
of the house.

705
01:16:12,972 --> 01:16:15,391
这个屋子有很多心脏
This house has many hearts.

706
01:16:17,685 --> 01:16:19,812
- 怎么啦?
- 怎么啦?
- What is the matter?
- What's the matter?

707
01:16:22,440 --> 01:16:25,151
我试图用我的意念来回答她...
I was trying to answer her
with my mind...

708
01:16:25,235 --> 01:16:27,278
但她听不见我
and she couldn't hear me.

709
01:16:27,320 --> 01:16:30,323
我记得你说过坦基纳 柏恩
具有透视能力
I thought you said this Tangina Barrons
was an extraordinary clairvoyant.

710
01:16:30,406 --> 01:16:31,741
我是有
I am.

711
01:16:33,701 --> 01:16:36,704
我只是不喜欢欺骗性的答案
I just don't like trick answers.

712
01:16:45,338 --> 01:16:46,881
过来，亲爱的...
Come here, honey...

713
01:16:47,882 --> 01:16:49,884
把你的手给我
and give me your hand.

714
01:16:51,302 --> 01:16:53,263
我不会伤到你的
I'm not gonna bite you.

715
01:17:04,065 --> 01:17:08,027
低下来点，让我能够俯视你
Come on down here. You'll give me
a whiplash lookin' up at you.

716
01:17:13,616 --> 01:17:16,911
你女儿还活在这间屋子里
Your daughter is alive
and in this house.

717
01:17:29,340 --> 01:17:32,302
最后一次事件发生在哪里?
Where was the last incident
of bilocation?

718
01:17:39,392 --> 01:17:41,936
我强烈感觉到...
I get my strongest feelin'...

719
01:17:41,936 --> 01:17:46,357
源头起于孩子楼上的壁橱
the point of origin is in
the child's closet upstairs.

720
01:17:47,233 --> 01:17:50,486
是的，我也这样相信
Yes. I believe that too.

721
01:17:50,528 --> 01:17:55,492
亲爱的，你要为了我和为了你
的女儿而坚强点
Honey, you're gonna be strong for me
and for your daughter.

722
01:17:55,533 --> 01:18:01,388
没有了你的信心和对孩子的爱，
我什么都做不了...
I can do absolutely nothing
without your faith in this world...
and your love for the children.

723
01:18:01,414 --> 01:18:03,958
我会的，相信我，我会的
I will.
Believe me, I will.

724
01:18:03,958 --> 01:18:10,981
那你会照我说的做吗？即使违背了
你作为一个人类和基督徒的信仰
And will you do anything I ask,
even if it comes contrary...
to your beliefs as a human being
and a Christian?

725
01:18:10,965 --> 01:18:13,551
是的，我会的
Yes, I promise. Please!

726
01:18:20,642 --> 01:18:22,560
你们都过来好吗?
Would you all come on in?

727
01:18:23,394 --> 01:18:24,687
聚在一起
Gather 'round.

728
01:18:29,442 --> 01:18:31,402
这里没有死亡
There is no death.

729
01:18:32,695 --> 01:18:37,992
只是另一种不同的意识的转换
It is only a transition to
a different sphere of consciousness.

730
01:18:38,117 --> 01:18:42,330
卡罗尔和她身边的东西不同
Carol Anne is not like those
she's with.

731
01:18:43,706 --> 01:18:46,417
她是活生生地生存着的...
She is a living presence...

732
01:18:46,459 --> 01:18:49,879
在他们的精神空间里
in their spiritual earthbound plane.

733
01:18:49,963 --> 01:18:53,842
他们被她的一样东西所吸引...
They are attracted
to the one thing about her...

734
01:18:53,883 --> 01:18:59,013
对他们来说完全不同--
她的生命力
that is different from themselves--
her life force.

735
01:18:59,055 --> 01:19:01,641
非常强大
It is very strong.

736
01:19:01,724 --> 01:19:05,144
它散发出自己的光芒
It gives off
its own illumination.

737
01:19:05,186 --> 01:19:08,648
它意味着生命的光辉...
It is a light that implies life...

738
01:19:08,731 --> 01:19:11,192
爱和家庭的回忆...
and memory of love and home...

739
01:19:12,610 --> 01:19:14,571
和现世的快乐--
and earthly pleasures--

740
01:19:15,780 --> 01:19:18,616
这是他们绝对渴望的...
something they
desperately desire...

741
01:19:19,659 --> 01:19:21,744
但却再也没有的
but can't have anymore.

742
01:19:23,329 --> 01:19:26,666
现在，她最靠近...
Right now, she's the closest thing
to that...

743
01:19:27,917 --> 01:19:31,754
那个可怕的娱乐物...
and that is
a terrible distraction...

744
01:19:31,796 --> 01:19:35,884
有着来自他们的真实光线
from the real light
that has finally come for them.

745
01:19:37,093 --> 01:19:39,220
你听懂我说的吗?
Do you understand me?

746
01:19:42,390 --> 01:19:47,979
这些灵魂，不知什么原因，没有停息...
These souls, who for
whatever reason are not at rest...

747
01:19:48,062 --> 01:19:51,482
也没有意识到他们已经死了
are also not aware
that they have passed on.

748
01:19:52,692 --> 01:19:56,529
他们不是我们所知的意识
They're not part of consciousness
as we know it.

749
01:19:56,613 --> 01:19:59,908
他们永远徘徊于一种梦幻状态...
They linger in
a perpetual dream state...

750
01:20:00,992 --> 01:20:04,078
一个他们永远醒不来的噩梦中
a nightmare from which
they cannot awake.

751
01:20:05,246 --> 01:20:10,251
在七色光中是超度--
Inside the spectral light
is salvation--

752
01:20:11,503 --> 01:20:14,380
隔着窗口看来世
a window to the next plane.

753
01:20:14,422 --> 01:20:16,549
他们必须穿过这层隔膜...
They must pass through
this membrane...

754
01:20:16,674 --> 01:20:20,929
那里有朋友等着引导他们去新的目的地
where friends are waiting
to guide them to new destinies.

755
01:20:22,555 --> 01:20:25,850
卡罗尔必须帮助他们去穿越...
Carol Anne must help them
cross over...

756
01:20:25,934 --> 01:20:30,813
而她只能听见她母亲的声音
and she will only hear
her mother's voice.

757
01:20:34,317 --> 01:20:35,443
现在...
Now...

758
01:20:36,569 --> 01:20:38,821
要坚持住
hold on to yourselves.

759
01:20:43,034 --> 01:20:44,994
还有件事
There's one more thing.

760
01:20:46,579 --> 01:20:49,833
一个可怕的东西在那里和她在一起
A terrible presence
is in there with her.

761
01:20:50,750 --> 01:20:55,171
非常粗暴，非常狂野
So much rage.
So much betrayal.

762
01:20:55,255 --> 01:20:58,424
我以前从没感受过它这样的
I've never sensed
anything like it.

763
01:20:59,717 --> 01:21:02,846
我不知道什么东西盘旋在这个屋子里...
I don't know
what hovers over this house...

764
01:21:02,887 --> 01:21:06,641
但是它有足够的能力打个洞
来到这个世界...
but it was strong enough to punch
a hole into this world...

765
01:21:06,724 --> 01:21:08,726
并带走你们的女儿
and take your daughter
away from you.

766
01:21:10,645 --> 01:21:14,607
它使卡罗尔非常靠近它...
It keeps Carol Anne
very close to it...

767
01:21:14,649 --> 01:21:17,026
远离七色光
and away from the spectral light.

768
01:21:17,902 --> 01:21:20,488
它对她说谎
It lies to her.

769
01:21:20,488 --> 01:21:24,742
它说些只有孩子听得懂的话
It says things
only a child can understand.

770
01:21:24,784 --> 01:21:28,288
它利用她来控制其它幽灵
It has been usin' her
to restrain the others.

771
01:21:30,206 --> 01:21:35,336
对她来说，它只是另一个孩子
To her, it simply is
another child.

772
01:21:37,630 --> 01:21:41,509
对我们来说，它是个野兽
To us, it is the beast.

773
01:21:56,524 --> 01:21:58,610
现在，让我们来找回你女儿
Now let's go get your daughter.

774
01:22:03,364 --> 01:22:07,535
红缎带, 手帕, 网球
Red ribbons,
handkerchiefs, tennis balls.

775
01:22:07,619 --> 01:22:09,537
好的，绳子准备好了
Okay, rope's ready.

776
01:22:09,621 --> 01:22:12,499
- 浴缸里的水呢?
- 我关了，也已经准备好了
- Bathwater?
- I shut it off. It's ready too.

777
01:22:12,540 --> 01:22:15,543
好的，呼叫她吧
All right. Call to her.

778
01:22:25,428 --> 01:22:27,722
卡罗尔, 我是妈妈，
你听得见我吗？
Carol Anne, it's Mommy.
Can you hear me?

779
01:22:32,519 --> 01:22:34,687
卡罗尔,
请对妈妈说hello
Carol Anne,
please tell Mommy hello.

780
01:22:36,731 --> 01:22:38,733
再试试
Try again.

781
01:22:40,568 --> 01:22:42,570
你能对爸爸说声Hello吗?
Can you say hello to Daddy?

782
01:22:43,821 --> 01:22:46,115
我和你爸爸都很想你
Daddy and I miss you so much.

783
01:22:47,325 --> 01:22:50,161
我们都非常想你，
So much. We love you so much.

784
01:22:50,286 --> 01:22:52,413
只要说声Hello
Please, just say hello.

785
01:22:52,455 --> 01:22:55,166
- 她被压抑住了
- 什么?
- She's under restraint.
- What?

786
01:22:55,291 --> 01:22:58,127
- 谁在压抑她?
- 她被许多手臂围住了
- Who's restraining her?
- There are many arms about her.

787
01:22:58,169 --> 01:23:02,882
她认为很安全。你们谁更能威吓到她？
你还是你丈夫？
She thinks it's safe. Who is she more
threatened by, you or your husband?

788
01:23:02,966 --> 01:23:05,885
都不行。史迪夫判定对孩子们的惩罚--
Neither. Steve decides
the punishment the children--

789
01:23:05,969 --> 01:23:07,887
不公平，我从没打过他们--
That's not fair.
I've never laid a hand--

790
01:23:07,971 --> 01:23:11,182
以后再吵，史迪夫,
让卡罗尔回答你们
Fight about it later.
Steven, make Carol Anne answer you.

791
01:23:14,477 --> 01:23:16,437
对她生气
Be cross with her.

792
01:23:16,479 --> 01:23:18,189
我是爸爸
It's Daddy.

793
01:23:18,314 --> 01:23:20,900
对她发怒,否则你将再也见不到她
Be angry with her,
or you'll never see her again.

794
01:23:20,984 --> 01:23:23,570
卡罗尔, 我要你回答我
Carol Anne, I want you
to answer me.

795
01:23:23,611 --> 01:23:26,739
告诉她，如果她不回答你，
你会打她屁股
Tell her if she doesn't answer you,
she'll get a spankin'.

796
01:23:26,781 --> 01:23:29,742
- 我从不打孩子们
- 亲爱的，不要这样，告诉她
- I've never spanked the children.
- Honey, please. Just tell her.

797
01:23:32,787 --> 01:23:35,331
卡罗尔,你快回答你的父母...
Carol Anne,
you answer your parents...

798
01:23:35,456 --> 01:23:37,917
否则我们都会狠狠地打你屁股
or you're gonna get
a real spanking from the both of us!

799
01:23:37,959 --> 01:23:40,044
妈妈! 救我!
Mommy! Help me!

800
01:23:41,296 --> 01:23:45,216
- 她离开了他
- 离开了谁? 她还好吗?
- She's away from him.
- From whom? Is she all right?

801
01:23:45,300 --> 01:23:47,218
达尼, 问问灯的事
Diane, ask about the light.

802
01:23:50,180 --> 01:23:52,098
妈妈，请救我!
Mommy, help me, please!

803
01:23:54,225 --> 01:23:57,187
- 亲爱的，你看见一盏灯了吗?
- 请救救我!
- Honey, do you see a light?
- Help me, please!

804
01:23:57,228 --> 01:23:59,189
妈妈，请救我!
Mommy! Help me!

805
01:23:59,230 --> 01:24:01,983
告诉她，去灯那里
Tell her to go to the light.

806
01:24:03,693 --> 01:24:06,487
他们会跟着她，
他们已经跟着她几个星期了
They'll follow her. They've been
followin' her for weeks.

807
01:24:06,529 --> 01:24:09,532
- 你必须照我说的做!
- 告诉她, 达尼.
- You must do what I say!
- Tell her, Diane.

808
01:24:09,532 --> 01:24:12,535
妈妈，我找不到你!
Mommy, I can't find you!

809
01:24:12,619 --> 01:24:15,538
跑向灯光那里!
用你最快的速度!
Run to the light!
Run as fast as you can!

810
01:24:15,663 --> 01:24:17,540
- 我就在灯光里!
- 不，亲爱的
- I am in the light!
- No, honey.

811
01:24:17,665 --> 01:24:19,709
- 告诉她，你在灯光里
- 不，这是谎言!
- Tell her you are.
- No, it's a lie!

812
01:24:19,834 --> 01:24:23,379
当你的孩子处于困境中，
你可以帮助她选择生或死
You can't choose between life and death
when dealin' with what is in between.

813
01:24:23,505 --> 01:24:25,381
告诉她，否则会太晚了
Tell her before it's too late.

814
01:24:26,216 --> 01:24:28,676
孩子，跑向灯光那里
Run to the light, baby.

815
01:24:28,718 --> 01:24:31,304
- 妈妈就在灯光里
- 告诉她，你在等她
- Mommy is in the light.
- Tell her you're waiting for her.

816
01:24:31,387 --> 01:24:34,641
妈妈正在灯光里等你。
我讨厌这样做
Mommy is waiting for you in the light.
I hate you for this.

817
01:24:35,850 --> 01:24:39,145
现在什么都别想，它知道什么能使你害怕
Now clear your minds.
It knows what scares you.

818
01:24:39,229 --> 01:24:41,564
它从一开始就知道
It has from the very beginning.

819
01:24:41,648 --> 01:24:44,234
不要给它任何帮助。
它已经知道的够多了
Don't give it any help.
It knows too much already.

820
01:24:45,693 --> 01:24:47,737
现在，打开门
Now, open the door.

821
01:25:23,565 --> 01:25:28,319
赖安, 下楼去等待目标!
Ryan, get downstairs
and wait by the target!

822
01:25:31,614 --> 01:25:35,618
给我标记1的网球!
Give me the tennis ball
marked number 1 !

823
01:26:11,654 --> 01:26:15,783
莱斯博士! 是我的笔迹!
它凭空出现了!
Dr. Lesh! It's my handwriting!
It came right out of thin air!

824
01:26:16,951 --> 01:26:19,829
球回来了，是他的笔迹!
The ball came back.
It's his handwriting!

825
01:26:27,670 --> 01:26:29,297
他妈的!
Kiss my ass!

826
01:26:29,380 --> 01:26:31,090
2号球!
Number 2!

827
01:26:32,383 --> 01:26:34,552
把你的手递过来!
Give me your hand!

828
01:26:57,575 --> 01:27:00,453
她就在走廊口!
She's at the mouth
of the corridor!

829
01:27:00,537 --> 01:27:05,166
告诉她停下!
叫她不要走到灯里去!
Tell her to stop!
Tell her not to go into the light!

830
01:27:07,460 --> 01:27:12,423
听我说，不要走进灯里去
Listen to me.
Do not go into the light.

831
01:27:12,465 --> 01:27:15,468
不管你在哪里，停下来。
转过身去
Stop where you are.
Turn away from it.

832
01:27:15,593 --> 01:27:17,345
甚至不要再看灯了
Don't even look at it.

833
01:27:17,428 --> 01:27:20,014
绳子快点!
Hurry with the rope!

834
01:27:23,726 --> 01:27:26,271
扔到灯光里去!
Throw it into the light!

835
01:27:34,320 --> 01:27:36,197
太棒了
Fantastic.

836
01:27:37,323 --> 01:27:38,491
我拿到了!
I got it!

837
01:27:39,909 --> 01:27:43,746
告诉他慢慢拉绳子
Tell him
to take up the slack gently.

838
01:27:43,788 --> 01:27:45,206
拉绳子!
Take up the slack!

839
01:27:46,082 --> 01:27:48,042
拉绳子!
Take up the slack!

840
01:28:13,943 --> 01:28:16,529
帮我把这围在我腰上!
Help me tie this around my waist!

841
01:28:16,654 --> 01:28:18,072
你要干什么?
What are you doing?

842
01:28:18,114 --> 01:28:21,242
我去把她带回来!
I'm goin' in after her!

843
01:28:21,367 --> 01:28:24,078
她不会跟你走的!
我去吧!
She won't come to you!
Let me go!

844
01:28:24,120 --> 01:28:26,915
你以前从没做过!
You've never done this before!

845
01:28:26,956 --> 01:28:28,541
你也没有!
Neither have you!

846
01:28:29,626 --> 01:28:31,628
你是对的，你去
You're right. You go.

847
01:28:32,629 --> 01:28:33,963
不，让我去!
No! Let me!

848
01:28:34,005 --> 01:28:37,133
你不行！这里只有你足够
强壮能拉住绳子
You can't! Who's strong enough
to stay here and hold the rope?

849
01:29:03,701 --> 01:29:05,703
我爱你!
I love you!

850
01:29:05,745 --> 01:29:10,708
不! 到楼下去和赖安一起等...
